==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dunder
<hw>Dun"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>redundar</ets> to overflow.]</ety> <def>The lees or dregs of cane
juice, used in the distillation of rum.</def> <mark>[West
Indies]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The use of <qex>dunder</qex> in the making of rum answers the
purpose of yeast in the fermentation of flour.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Edwards.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dunderhead</ent>⟦br⟧
